Z&O tuning to the max. Overall theme is making the deck a bit slower with less ramp, but more "methodical" in being able to get lethal in if i need to
- Mox Diamond (didnt ever like losing land drops)
- Chrome Mox (bad overall, not enough colored spells and losing a card is bad)
- Mystic Remora (alright, but I'm using mana a lot in early turns so I found letting it go after 1, which after that its a dead spell)
- Blood Mist (double strike was nice, but i always found 4 mana to be awkward on tempo)
- Dack Fayden (thought i'd steal some mana rocks, but overall pretty underwhelming)
- Seething Song (fast, but meh)
- Sword of Feast and Famine (thought it could be a backup wincon with aggrevated assault, but never got there-- otherwise pretty meh. i want to spend mana before combat and its not the magic +3)
- Chromatic Lantern (droppin mana rocks)
- Distortion Strike (nto as good as the new replacements i just added)

+ Golbin Festival (this card is hilarious and flips coins. In particular added this because my Karplusan minotaur was used politically and i thought that was fun; this should be similar hopefully)
+ Whispersilk Cloak (i usually dont like this card, but figure unblockable and shroud is good enough here)
+ Leap (flying, draw a card, and INSTANT -- instant is important because i can choose to use it after flipping to see if it's lethal. Other shit like slip through space is sorcery... so i have to risk it)
+ Shadow Rift (same as leap)
+ Steam vents (adding lands is never bad)
+ Misdirection (more protection for Okaun)
+ Glen Elandra Archmage (more protection)
+ Transmute Artifact (getting the right artifact out like krark's thumb seems important)
+ Ral Zarek (taps blockers? untaps mana rocks? not sure if this will provide enough value. Ult is flip 5 coins....)
